  "prompt": "How do you find \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo?",
  "response": "Finding \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo can be a bit tricky since these platforms don't always prominently feature projects that haven't launched yet. However, here are some strategies to discover upcoming projects:\n\n### **On Kickstarter:**\n1. **Search Categories:**  \n   - Browse through categories that interest you and look for projects that are labeled \"preview\" or \"coming soon.\" These are often visible in the \"Coming Soon\" section of certain categories.\n\n2. **Project Creators\u2019 Social Media:**  \n   - Follow creators or brands you\u2019re interested in on social media platforms like Twitter, Instagram, or Facebook. Many creators promote their upcoming projects before they launch.\n\n3. **Email Notifications:**  \n   - Sign up for Kickstarter\u2019s newsletter or follow specific categories to receive notifications about upcoming projects.\n\n4. **Explore \"Projects We Love\":**  \n   - Kickstarter\u2019s \"Projects We Love\" section sometimes includes previews of projects that haven\u2019t launched yet.\n\n5. **Use Third-Party Websites:**  \n   - Websites like **BackerKit** or **Crowdfundr** sometimes list upcoming Kickstarter projects.\n\n### **On Indiegogo:**\n1. **Explore the Platform:**  \n   - Check out the \"Upcoming\" section or browse through categories to find projects that are listed as \"pre-launch\" or \"coming soon.\"\n\n2. **Follow Creators:**  \n   - If you\u2019ve backed a creator before, follow their profile to get notified of their upcoming campaigns.\n\n3. **Sign Up for Emails:**  \n   - Subscribe to Indiegogo\u2019s newsletter to receive updates on new and upcoming projects.\n\n4. **Search for Specific Niches:**  \n   - Use keywords related to your interests (e.g., \"tech,\" \"fashion,\" \"games\") and filter by \"upcoming\" projects if available.\n\n5. **Third-Party Aggregators:**  \n   - Websites like **Gadget Flow** or **Crowdfund Insider** often highlight upcoming Indiegogo campaigns.\n\n### **General Tips:**\n- Use search engines to look for \"upcoming Kickstarter/Indiegogo projects\" followed by your area of interest (e.g., \"upcoming Indiegogo tech projects\").\n- Join crowdfunding communities on Reddit (e.g., r/kickstarter, r/Indiegogo) or Facebook groups where creators and backers discuss upcoming campaigns.\n- Check out crowdfunding blogs and websites that curate and highlight trending or upcoming projects.\n\nBy combining these methods, you can stay ahead of the curve and discover exciting \"coming soon\" projects on both platforms!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
